CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 2, 1962, pg. 11 reads: "How Are They? - As soon as the snow has left the ground, Mrs. Jayne McDaniel and her mother, Mrs. Cornelia Brooks, hurry out to the backyard of the McDaniel home, to see what damage has been done to the rose bushes, the pet hobby of Mrs. McDaniel's husband, Luke. This picture was taken several months ago before spring had transformed the dull grey to beautiful green. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Jayne McDaniel, kneeling down, and Cornelia Brooks, members of the Knotty Pine garden club, gathered in garden
